pr_body:
Modified the defaultValidators.js file to add the following validations - 
1. Nodes adhere to the naming style, Nodename:program. For example, this can be, "CZ:controller.py" where CZ is the node name and controller.py is the program name. A Nodename such as "AB" will fail since there is no ":" in the name of the node whereas "AB:ab" will succeed.
2. No two nodes can be created with the same Nodename. That means, two nodes cannot be named as "CZ:controller.py" and "CZ:optimizer.py" since CZ is there a duplicate.

1. Added the react-keyed-file-browser package to show the folder structure of concore.
2. Added support for opening multiple files simultaneously.

pr_title: Implementation of save feature in Edge/Chrome
pr_body:
With respect to issue #14 it addresses points 1-13 and 17.
Major features in this PR
1. Hierarchical folder structure
2. Saving the files directly from Chrome/Edge
3. Custom open folder button (automatically switches between File API and File System Access API based on browser).
